Included files:
	 1.lab4b.c: source file that implements specified functionalities of this project.
	 2.Makefile: this makefile supports four targets:
	 	     (default): used to compile the source code to a program named lab0
		     check: execute an automated smoke-test to see if it runs and can talk to its sensors
		     clean: delete all files created by Makefile
		     dist: build the distribution tarball
	3.README: descriptions of each of the included files && comments on the submission

Smoke-test in the check target:
it provides the following input for the program:
SCALE=C
PERIOD=2
STOP
START
LOG helloworld
OFF

The test checks the following things:
1.the program runs successfully
2.the timestamp and temperature are recorded
3.each of the command is recorded
4.the final SHUTDOWN is recorded

RESEARCH:
How to print time format:
